text: Question when I export a hubDB as a CSV and a colleague import is in his sandbox only Name is imported; does anybody know why and how we can fix this

Hey all, this may have been asked before, but couldn't find anything helpful.

I'm building a partner directory/locator. I am filtering data in my HubDB table to show partners based on user selections.

I want to filter the data without having to refresh the page. I assume I could do something like this via AJAX, but couldn't find any helpful information related to HubDB and AJAX.

Has anyone done this before or have some tips regarding this?

In such case I am using Vue Js and Axios and Lodash library, It will make my work easierâ€¦..
but you have to write logic by your own :slightly_smiling_face:
<@U2H3TT8F2> this seems to have resolved itself?? Is there a changelog we could send over to verify what may have happened?
I can look into this and see.  <@U01AEL2C0VD> can you send me a link in a DM to your portal for this module so I can pop in there and take a look
Import does not automatically create the table columns for you.. You need to create table with all the columns and them import it.
Alternatively, to make this easier, you can use HubSpot CLI to get the hubdb data and then upload it to a new portal
